   386→                        <div id="content">Let $R(n;k,r)$ be the smallest $N$ such that if the edges of $K_N$ are $r$-coloured then there is a set of $n$ vertices which does not contain a copy of $K_k$ in at least one of the $r$ colours. Prove that there is a constant $C=C(r)&#62;1$ such that\[R(n;3,r) &#60; C^{\sqrt{n}}.\]</div>
